TY  - JOUR
T1  - Formulating Technology Policy and Planning Industrial R&D Activities
AU  - Oral, Muhittin
AU  - Malouin, Jean-Louis
AU  - Rahn, Joël
Y1  - 1981/11/01
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.27.11.1294
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.27.11.1294
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1294
EP  - 1308
VL  - 27
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper summarizes an actual study conducted for the State Planning Organization of Turkey with the objective of formulating a national R&D policy, the implementation of which will contribute to the realization of the national goals stated in the development plans of the country. The study consists of three complementary substudies: (i) a continuous simulation model for evaluating national technology policy, (ii) an industrial survey to determine the structure of technology employed in production units, (iii) a plan for R&D activities in the iron and steel industry. A ?macro-to-micro and micro-to-macro? approach was used in conducting the study in order to base the concepts on the facts and to find the facts based on the concepts.
AB  - This paper summarizes an actual study conducted for the State Planning Organization of Turkey with the objective of formulating a national R&D policy, the implementation of which will contribute to the realization of the national goals stated in the development plans of the country. The study consists of three complementary substudies: (i) a continuous simulation model for evaluating national technology policy, (ii) an industrial survey to determine the structure of technology employed in production units, (iii) a plan for R&D activities in the iron and steel industry. A ?macro-to-micro and micro-to-macro? approach was used in conducting the study in order to base the concepts on the facts and to find the facts based on the concepts.
